    "summary": "After > 20 years of experience in marketing and category management within the FMCG business I decided to start my own business in marketing consulting in May 2022. One of my key drivers has been to share my knowledge and experience to help others. I am available for diverse marketing and communication projects in both profit and non-profit sectors. Facilitating workshops as a marketing specialist to develop a brand strategy and commercial plan for JPG Hulsebosch and working a.i. at Longfonds to develop a communication strategy are examples of the assignments I have done. I love to cooperate with diverse types of people and am passionate about building strong, sustainable brand stories to make companies and organizations more successful. I have a hands on mentality and like to combine hard working with a hint of humor every day.\n\nIn my latest role as a Marketing Manager at Dr. Oetker, I was leading the multidisciplinary business team 'Cake & Desserts' next to my marketing role to lead and coach the brand teams for Dr. Oetker Baking and Koopmans. Responsible for business growth, new business development, brand and innovation strategy, impactful campaigns and customer experience marketing; passionate about people and brands.\n\nBefore I worked at Unilever and Sara Lee/Douwe Egberts in several (non)-food categories.\n\nSpecialties: business and brand strategy, communication/ activation, NPD, coaching teams.",
